    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-14T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-14T20:00:00-05:00" n="268"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.51/1258.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Minister
                            <persName type="to">Sullivan</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-14T20:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1914, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your March 5, 10 a.m. and March 10, 1 p.m. Department encounters difficulty in
                    arranging temporary advance of $500,000 to Dominican Government without definite
                    guaranty and is willing to endeavor to arrange the advance provided the
                    Dominican Government will pledge and turn over the collection of alcohol and
                    tobacco taxes to the Receivership.</p>
                <p>Do you intend to convey by your use of word tobacco tax that it is the tax based
                    solely on tobacco, or is it the tax on stamps which, it is understood, embodies
                    tax on tobacco.</p>
                <p>We are still looking for a commercial attaché.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
